# Introverted vs. Extroverted

When the phone rings, do you
-E hurry to get it first
-I hope someone else will answer

Waiting in line, do you often
-E chat with others
-I stick to business

At a party, do you
-E interact with many, even strangers
-I interact with a few friends

Does interacting with strangers
-E energize you
-I tax your reserves

Do you tend to
-E say right out what's on your mind
-I keep your ears open

Do you think of yourself as
-E an outgoing person
-I a private person

Are you the kind of person who
-E is rather talkative
-I doesn't miss much

At work, do you tend to
-E be sociable with your colleagues
-I keep more to yourself

Do you consider yourself
-E a good conversationalist
-I a good listener

Are you inclined to be
-E easy to approach
-I somewhat reserved

In your social groups, do you
-E keep abreast of others' happenings
-I get behind on the news

# Sensing vs. Intuitive

Are you more
-S observant than introspective
-N introspective than observant

Is it worse to
-S have your head in the clouds
-N be in a rut

Are you more
-S sensible than ideational
-N ideational than sensible

Are you more interested in
-S what is actual
-N what is possible

Do you tend to be more
-S factual than speculative
-N speculative than factual

Do you like writers who
-S say what they mean
-N use metaphors and symbolism

Facts
-S speak for themselves
-N illustrate principles

Do you find visionaries and theorists
-S somewhat annoying
-N rather fascinating

Common sense is
-S usually reliable
-N frequently questionable

Children often do not
-S make themselves useful enough
-N exercise their fantasy enough

Are you more frequently
-S a practical sort of person
-N a fanciful sort of person

Do you speak more in
-S particulars than generalities
-N generalities than particulars

Are you inclined to take what is said
-S more literally
-N more figuratively

Do you more often see
-S what's right in front of you
-N what can only be imagined

Are you more likely to trust
-S your experiences
-N your conceptions

Are you more inclined to feel
-S down to earth
-N somewhat removed

Do you prize in yourself
-S a strong hold on reality
-N a vivid imagination

Are you drawn more to
-S fundamentals
-N overtones

In stories, do you prefer
-S action and adventure
-N fantasy and heroism

Is it easier for you to
-S put others to good use
-N identify with others

Are you more interested in
-S production and distribution
-N design and research

# Thinking vs. Feeling

With people, are you usually more
-T firm than gentle
-F gentle than firm

Are you more comfortable in making
-T critical judgments
-F value judgments

In making up your mind, are you more likely to go by
-T data
-F desires

In sizing up others, do you tend to be
-T objective and impersonal
-F friendly and personal

Which appeals to you more
-T consistency of thought
-F harmonious relationships

If you must disappoint someone, are you usually
-T frank and straightforward
-F warm and considerate

In a heated discussion, do you
-T stick to your guns
-F look for common ground

Is it better to be
-T just
-F merciful

When in charge of others, do you tend to be
-T firm and unbending
-F forgiving and lenient

Are you more often
-T a cool-headed person
-F a warm-hearted person

Which is more of a compliment
-T There's a logical person
-F There's a sentimental person

Which rules you more
-T your thoughts
-F your feelings

Is it worse to be
-T a softy
-F hard-nosed

In trying circumstances, are you sometimes
-T too unsympathetic
-F too sympathetic

Do you think of yourself as a
-T tough-minded person
-F tender-hearted person

Do you value in yourself more that you are
-T reasonable
-F devoted

Which seems the greater fault
-T to be too compassionate
-F to be too dispassionate

Are you swayed more by
-T convincing evidence
-F a touching appeal

Which do you wish more for yourself
-T strength of will
-F strength of emotion

Do you see yourself as basically
-T thick-skinned
-F thin-skinned

In judging others, are you more swayed by
-T laws than circumstances
-F circumstances than laws

# Judging vs. Perceiving

Is clutter in the workplace something you
-J take time to straighten up
-P tolerate pretty well

Is it your way to
-J make up your mind quickly
-P pick and choose at some length

Do you prefer contracts to be
-J signed, sealed and delivered
-P settled on a handshake

Are you more satisfied having
-J a finished product
-P work in progress

Do you like things
-J scheduled
-P unscheduled

Do you often prefer
-J final, unalterable statements
-P tentative, preliminary statements

At work, is it more natural for you to
-J point out mistakes
-P try to please others

Are you more comfortable
-J after a decision
-P before a decision

Are you prone to
-J nailing things down
-P exploring the possibilities

In most situations, are you more
-J deliberate than spontaneous
-P spontaneous than deliberate

When finishing a job, do you like to
-J tie up all the loose ends
-P move on to something else

Do you prefer to work
-J to deadlines
-P just whenever

Do you tend to choose
-J rather carefully
-P somewhat impulsively

Are you inclined to be more
-J hurried than leisurely
-P leisurely than hurried

Do you usually want things
-J settled and decided
-P just penciled in

Would you say you are more
-J serious and determined
-P easy going

Do you feel better about
-J coming to closure
-P keeping your options open

Is it preferable mostly to
-J make sure things are arranged
-P just let things happen naturally

Do you tend to notice
-J disorderliness
-P opportunities for change

Are you more
-J routinized than whimsical
-P whimsical than routinized

Which is more admirable
-J the ability to organize and be methodical
-P the ability to adapt and make do
